                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf.184.015/104a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                        to the Chief of the Mission to the Baltic Provinces</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Greene</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-04">August 4,
                            1919</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>87. From Tyler: Baltic Commission recalled Colonel Greene and personnel to
                    proceed to Paris to report to Ammission, after winding up affairs of
                    Commission.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>] <hi
                        rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
